cost-effective solution without affecting the performance of a web application hosted in an Auto Scaling group of EC2 instances.

auto scaling

Step scaling policies and simple scaling policies are two of the dynamic scaling options available for you to use. Both require you to create CloudWatch alarms for the scaling policies.

target tracking scaling: increase or decrease the current capacity of the group based on a target value for a specific metric.adds or removes capacity as required to keep the metric at, or close to, the specified target value.

scheduled scaling: predictable traffic patterns.

simple scaling: need to wait for the cooldown period to complete before initiating additional scaling activities.

suspend and resume scaling: temporarily pause scaling activities triggered by your scaling policies and scheduled actions.

